The 68-year-old scientist and human rights activist died Thursday of an apparent heart attack in his Moscow apartment. World leaders from President Bush to President Mikhail S. In Brussels, the NATO foreign ministers hailed Sakharov as a pioneer who helped change Soviet society.  Gorbachev today praised Andrei D. He was just a remarkable person, said British Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher. The Soviet Congress stood for a minute of silence for their colleague, once considered a national hero for discovering the Soviet hydrogen bomb but later reviled by Kremlin leadership for his uncompromising stands for human freedom. 